title: How Did Rabbit, Rabbit Get Approved By Netflix? AHStories Theory Video

Netflix: Gets 'Rabbit Rabbit' in their platform

The whole world watching 'Rabbit Rabbit': Apocalypse II: Electric Boogaloo
Larry bought a Rolls instead of a home because he knew his days were numbered once the film got out. Sooo, he bought his dream car and said FUCK IT 🤷🏽‍♀️.

Maybe the Director had someone he knows from Netflix working with him... it's almost like the Twilight Zone where you have to come up with your own explanation...   Not everything is explained,  you have to use your imagination...   also I've been very disappointed with this American Horror Stories ...I think they're just aiming for a younger generation...  I still enjoy them but they are not out to please the people who are over 30
